parseAlignments

public static Alignment parseAlignments(List<String> outSentence,
                                        List<String> inSentence,
                                        String specs,
                                        boolean swap,
                                        Alignment a)
Reads an alignment of the form ([indexOfInWord]-[indexOfOutWord])* e.g. In : une phrase en francais Out: a french sentence would be represented by: "0-0 1-2 3-1" If swap is set to true, the format is assumed to be flipped: ([indexOfOutWord]-[indexOfInWord])* If swap is not specified, it is assumed to be false.

Parameters:
outSentence -
inSentence -

swap -
